---
import ClaudeCodeLayout from "../../layouts/ClaudeCodeLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/quickstart-shared.css";
---

<ClaudeCodeLayout
  title="Claude Code Quickstart — Up and Running in 10 Minutes"
  description="Install Claude Code, connect it to your codebase, and run your first AI coding task in under 10 minutes."
  currentPage="quickstart"
>
  <div class="qs-wrapper">

    <header class="qs-hero">
      <span class="qs-hero__eyebrow">Claude Code · Getting Started</span>
      <h1 class="qs-hero__title">
        Quick<span class="qs-hero__accent">Start</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="qs-hero__desc">Anthropic's terminal-native AI coding agent. Understands your codebase, writes and edits code, runs commands. Works in any project, zero config required.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="qs-journey">

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">01</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Prerequisites</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Node.js 18+ and an API key</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">You need Node.js and an Anthropic API key. Get the key at console.anthropic.com.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd-group">
          <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>node --version</code></div>
        </div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">Then set your key: export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...</p>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">02</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Install</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Install Claude Code globally</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">One command. Installs the <code>claude</code> CLI globally.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code</code></div>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">03</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">First Run</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Navigate to a project and launch</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">Claude Code reads your files automatically. Just go to your project directory and run it.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd-group">
          <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>cd your-project</code></div>
          <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>claude</code></div>
        </div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">Interactive mode. Type your task and Claude Code will read, edit, and explain code.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step qs-step--active">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">04</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Verify</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">First task — no config needed</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">Skip the interactive mode for now. Run this one-shot command — it will read your entire codebase and respond immediately.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>claude --print "explain this codebase in 3 sentences and list the main entry points"</code></div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">--print mode is non-interactive, perfect for scripting and one-off questions.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="qs-milestone">
      <span class="qs-milestone__eyebrow">First Real Task</span>
      <h2 class="qs-milestone__title">Add a CLAUDE.md — unlock persistent context</h2>
      <p class="qs-milestone__desc">The single highest-leverage thing you can do. A CLAUDE.md in your repo root is automatically read by Claude Code every session. It becomes your permanent project context.</p>
      <div class="qs-milestone__steps">
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">1</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Create the file in your project root.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="qs-milestone__cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>claude --print "generate a CLAUDE.md for this project based on the codebase" > CLAUDE.md</code></div>
      <div class="qs-milestone__steps">
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">2</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Edit it to add your conventions, preferred patterns, and anything Claude should always know. Now every CC session starts informed.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="qs-next">
      <p class="qs-next__title">What next?</p>
      <div class="qs-next__grid">
        <a href="/claude-code/tips/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">⚡</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Tips & Tricks</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">--print pipelines, stdin, parallel agents, CI integration.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/claude-code/cheatsheet/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">📋</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Cheatsheet</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">Every flag, mode, and workflow at a glance.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/claude-code/changelog/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">🔔</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Changelog</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">Stay current with every Anthropic release.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/claude-code/configs/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">⚙️</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Configs</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">Permission modes, output formats, API settings.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.querySelectorAll('.qs-cmd').forEach(function(block) {
      var btn = document.createElement('button');
      btn.className = 'qs-cmd__copy';
      btn.textContent = 'copy';
      btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
        var code = block.querySelector('code');
        if (!code) return;
        var text = code.textContent.replace(/^\$\s*/, '').trim();
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(function() {
          btn.textContent = 'copied!';
          setTimeout(function() { btn.textContent = 'copy'; }, 1500);
        });
      });
      block.style.paddingRight = '5rem';
      block.appendChild(btn);
    });
  </script>
</ClaudeCodeLayout>
